# .NET API Project — Cursor Rules

## Tech Stack
- .NET 10 / C# 13 / ASP.NET Core
- Entity Framework Core with MSSQL
- xUnit + Moq + FluentAssertions for testing
- Serilog for structured logging
- FluentValidation for input validation
- MediatR for CQRS (if used — remove if not)
- AutoMapper for DTO mapping (if used — remove if not)

## Architecture
- Clean Architecture: API → Application → Domain → Infrastructure
- Controllers handle HTTP only (model binding, status codes, response mapping)
- Business logic lives in services or MediatR handlers
- Repository pattern for data access
- Dependency injection for all dependencies

## Code Standards
- File-scoped namespaces: `namespace ProjectName.Layer;`
- Nullable reference types: always enabled
- Async/await: always. Never `.Result`, `.Wait()`, or `.GetAwaiter().GetResult()`
- CancellationToken: accept on all async methods
- Private fields: underscore prefix (_logger, _repository, _service)
- Constants: PascalCase
- Interfaces: prefix with I (IUserService, IRepository<T>)
- DTOs: suffix with Dto (UserResponseDto, CreateUserRequestDto)

## Error Handling
- Use Result<T> pattern for business logic outcomes (not exceptions)
- Use ProblemDetails for HTTP error responses
- Global exception middleware for unhandled exceptions
- Never swallow exceptions silently
- Log errors before rethrowing; use `throw;` to preserve stack trace

## Security & Compliance (HIPAA)
- NEVER log PHI (patient names, DOBs, SSNs, prescription details, drug names)
- NEVER include PHI in error messages or exception details
- NEVER put PHI in URLs or query parameters
- All endpoints require [Authorize] unless explicitly [AllowAnonymous]
- Parameterize ALL database queries — no string concatenation for SQL
- Audit log all data mutations (who, what, when, from where)
- Validate all external inputs at the API boundary
- Use data annotations or FluentValidation on all request DTOs

## Database
- Use EF Core Fluent API for configuration (not data annotations on entities)
- Migrations: descriptive names (20260331_AddPrescriptionTransfers)
- Always include Down() method in migrations
- Use DateTimeOffset (not DateTime) for all timestamps
- Use Guid for primary keys (newsequentialid() default in SQL)

## Testing
- Test naming: MethodName_Scenario_ExpectedResult
- One assertion concept per test (multiple Assert calls for the same concept are fine)
- Use Moq for mocking dependencies
- Use builder patterns for test data
- Do NOT use real PHI in test data — use obviously fake data
- Unit tests for service/handler logic
- Integration tests for API endpoints (using WebApplicationFactory)

## Response Format
- Successful reads: 200 OK
- Successful creates: 201 Created with Location header
- Successful updates: 200 OK or 204 No Content
- Successful deletes: 204 No Content
- Validation errors: 400 Bad Request with ProblemDetails
- Not found: 404 Not Found
- Unauthorized: 401 Unauthorized
- Forbidden: 403 Forbidden

## When Generating Code
- Match the patterns in existing files — consistency matters more than "best practice"
- Include XML doc comments on all public classes, methods, and properties
- Register new services in DI (check existing registration patterns)
- Create both interface and implementation for new services
- Include unit tests for new service methods
